reviewText: True to life documentary of the overthrow of the Hawaiian monarchy without the sugar coating. It shows how and why decisions for Hawai'i were made by the monarchs as well as by the Americans. Very valuable tool to use for discussion on the overthrow. Highly recommended!!
Having been to the islands, I had to know about its history and how it became a state. Well, this dvd gave me a brief but accurate insight about that history.
